$ SQLite: transactions
@ transactions

By default, SQLite is in *autocommit mode*. In autocommit mode, each DML statement is commited when it finishes.
-
With `begin` (or the more verbose but equivalent `begin transaction`) statement, SQLite is taken out of autocommit mode.

{ Rolling back a create table #sqlite-rollback-create-table

  A → development/databases/SQLite/tables/create[create table] statement can be rolled back:
  gh|about-sqlite|/sql/transactions/create_table.sql||

}

sa:
  → development/databases/SQLite
